{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01ViTN6sLX2Tcc93eTDW79ZE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I can see the store has `self._relations` dict loaded in memory. I can either use `self._persistence.count_relations()` or count from the in-memory dict. The persistence layer's `count_relations` counts DB rows, while the in-memory `_relations` is per-entry. Let me use the persistence count for accuracy.\n\nNow I have all the information needed. Let me implement this in two repos:\n\n**tapps-brain changes:**\n1. Add `relation_count` to `StoreHealthReport`\n2. Add `count_relations()` method to `MemoryStore`  \n3. Populate `relation_count` in `health()`\n\n**TappsMCP changes:**\n1. Surface `relation_count` in `_handle_health()`\n2. Enable graph boost in `_ranked_search` when relation count >= 10\n\nLet me start with tapps-brain."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":353,"cache_read_input_tokens":54321,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":353},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"327621aa-924c-4bfb-b348-3a4acf890b54","uuid":"79fe057c-ab47-44ce-8a6d-71a166aee5ad"}
