{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Ds9yco4x2EWWZWkdKZd7ms","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `_apply_graph_boost` works on `list[dict[str, object]]` (injection-style memories with \"key\", \"score\" fields). The `_ranked_search` produces `ScoredMemory` objects. I need to apply the graph boost at the right abstraction level.\n\nThe cleanest approach: after getting `scored` results from `retriever.search()`, check relation count on the store, and if >= 10, apply graph boost using `store.find_related()`. I'll implement this directly in `_ranked_search` since the logic is simple and avoids coupling to `RecallOrchestrator`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1064,"cache_read_input_tokens":56743,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1064},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"327621aa-924c-4bfb-b348-3a4acf890b54","uuid":"476b0780-10f3-47ba-89e6-11405c36cecd"}
